to state four‐dimensionalism more clearly.","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00631.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00628.x","title":"The Normative Force of Reasoning","authors":["Ralph Wedgwood"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-11-06","volume":"40","issue":"4","pages":"660-686","abstract":"","topics":["ethics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00628.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00627.x","title":"Coincidence as Overlap 1","authors":["L. A. Paul"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-11-06","volume":"40","issue":"4","pages":"623-659","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00627.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00632.x","title":"Generic Essence, Objectual Essence, and Modality 1","authors":["Fabrice Correia"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-11-06","volume":"40","issue":"4","pages":"753-767","abstract":"","topics":["metaphysics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00632.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00624.x","title":"The 3D/4D Controversy: A Storm in a Teacup","authors":["Storrs McCall","E. J. Lowe"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"570-578","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00624.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00623.x","title":"The Determinable‐Determinate Relation","authors":["Eric Funkhouser"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"548-569","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00623.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00620.x","title":"Realism and the Meaning of ‘Real’ 1","authors":["Steven L. Reynolds"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"468-494","abstract":"","topics":["language","metaphysics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00620.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00622.x","title":"Does Informational Semantics Commit Euthyphro's Fallacy?","authors":["Jason Bridges"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"522-547","abstract":"","topics":["language"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00622.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00621.x","title":"Appearance Properties? 1","authors":["Andy Egan"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"495-521","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00621.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00619.x","title":"Is Mental Content Prior to Linguistic Meaning?","authors":["Jeff Speaks"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"428-467","abstract":"","topics":["language","mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00619.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00618.x","title":"Multiple‐Act Consequentialism","authors":["Joseph Mendola"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-08-04","volume":"40","issue":"3","pages":"395-427","abstract":"","topics":["ethics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0068.2006.00618.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00608.x","title":"Qualia ain’t in the head","authors":["Alex Byrne","Michael Tye"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"241-255","abstract":"","topics":["mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00608.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00614.x","title":"A Problem for a Direct‐Reference Theory of Belief Reports","authors":["Stephen Schiffer"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"361-368","abstract":"","topics":["epistemology","language"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00614.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00609.x","title":"Functionalism, Mental Causation, and the Problem of Metaphysically Necessary Effects 1","authors":["Robert D. Rupert"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"256-283","abstract":"","topics":["metaphysics","mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00609.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00610.x","title":"The Definition of Lying*","authors":["Thomas L. Carson"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"284-306","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00610.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00615.x","title":"The Resilience of Illogical Belief *","authors":["Nathan Salmon"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"369-375","abstract":"","topics":["epistemology"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00615.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00613.x","title":"The Value of Truth","authors":["Paul Horwich"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"347-360","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00613.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00607.x","title":"Sensory Awareness Is not a Wide Physical Relation: An Empirical Argument Against Externalist Intentionalism 1","authors":["Adam Pautz"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"205-240","abstract":"","topics":["epistemology"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00607.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00612.x","title":"A Defense of Reductionism about Testimonial Justification of Beliefs","authors":["Tomoji Shogenji"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"331-346","abstract":"This paper defends reductionism about testimonial justification of beliefs against two influential arguments. One is the empirical argument to the effect that the reductionist justification of our trust in testimony is either circular since it relies on testimonial evidence or else there is scarce evidence in support of our trust in testimony. The other is the transcendental argument to the effect that trust in testimony is a prerequisite for the very existence of testimonial evidence since without the presumption of people's truthfulness we cannot interpret their utterances as testimony with propositional contents. This paper contends that the epistemic subject can interpret utterances as testimony with propositional contents without presupposing the credibility of testimony, and that evidence available to the normal epistemic subject can justify her trust in testimony.","topics":["epistemology","language","social"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00612.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00611.x","title":"Moral Responsibility Without Libertarianism","authors":["Lynne Rudder Baker"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"307-330","abstract":"","topics":["ethics","political"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00611.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00616.x","title":"Illogical, But Rational","authors":["David Braun"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-05-08","volume":"40","issue":"2","pages":"376-379","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00616.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00601.x","title":"Can Empirical Theories of Semantic Competence Really Help Limn the Structure of Reality?","authors":["Steven Gross"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"43-81","abstract":"","topics":["language"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00601.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00606.x","title":"Scott Soames's Beyond Rigidity: The Unfinished Semantic Agenda of Naming and Necessity 1","authors":["Peter Hanks"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"184-203","abstract":"","topics":["language"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00606.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00604.x","title":"De Dicto Internalist Cognitivism*","authors":["Jon Tresan"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"143-165","abstract":"","topics":["epistemology","mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00604.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00603.x","title":"Epistemically Appropriate Perceptual Belief","authors":["Peter J. Markie"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"118-142","abstract":"","topics":["epistemology","mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00603.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00605.x","title":"Future Law: Prepunishment and the Causal Theory of Verdicts","authors":["Roy Sorensen"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"166-183","abstract":"","topics":["metaphysics","political"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00605.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00602.x","title":"Ambiguous Figures and the Content of Experience","authors":["Fiona Macpherson"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"82-117","abstract":"Representationalism is the position that the phenomenal character of an experience is either identical with, or supervenes on, the content of that experience. Many representationalists hold that the relevant content of experience is nonconceptual. I propose a counter‐example to this form of representationalism that arises from the phenomenon of Gestalt switching, which occurs when viewing ambiguous figures. First, I argue that one does not need to appeal to the conceptual content of experience or to judgements to account for Gestalt switching. I then argue that experiences of certain ambiguous figures are problematic because they have different phenomenal characters but that no difference in the nonconceptual content of these experiences can be identified. I consider three solutions to this problem that have been proposed by both philosophers and psychologists and conclude that none can account for all the ambiguous figures that pose the problem. I conclude that the onus is on representationalists to specify the relevant difference in content or to abandon their position.","topics":["mind"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00602.x"},{"doi":"10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00600.x","title":"Presupposition and Policing in Complex Demonstratives*","authors":["Michael Glanzberg","Susanna Siegel"],"journal":"nous","published":"2006-02-08","volume":"40","issue":"1","pages":"1-42","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.1111/j.0029-4624.2006.00600.x"}]